Business Viewpoint – SoilSense
1. Introduction

According to ISO/IEC 30141:2024, the Business Viewpoint focuses on understanding how an IoT system creates value, enables new services, and impacts stakeholders from a business perspective.

This viewpoint does not focus on implementation details such as hardware, protocols, or software components. Instead, it describes how the system contributes to operational goals, supports decision-making, and delivers benefits to its users and owners.

The analyzed system, SoilSense, is an IoT platform composed of ESP32-C6 sensor nodes, an OpenThread mesh network, a Gateway, a Border Router, a Matter Controller, and a Web/Mobile Dashboard for monitoring and control.

2. Executive Summary

SoilSense is an IoT solution designed to provide continuous environmental monitoring and remote control capabilities.

The system enables:

Humidity monitoring
Temperature monitoring
Water level monitoring
Remote pump control
Real-time visualization
Historical data storage
Alert and notification generation
Secure and scalable communication

By combining open technologies such as MQTT, CoAP, OpenThread, IPv6, and Matter, the platform provides a scalable and interoperable architecture capable of supporting future expansion.

